NAS_SRN_10pct.pdf":{},"TAKAFUL_TOB_NAS_SRN_20pct.pdf":{}}}},{"Rating":{"name":"Rating","type":"MARKDOWN","search":false,"table":false,"detail":false,"description":"","placeholder":"","order":"","andSearch":false,"rangeSearch":false,"children":["OverallQuality","Reason"]}},{"OverallQuality":{"name":"OverallQuality","type":"LABEL","search":true,"table":true,"detail":true,"description":{"template":"Default description for {}","variables":["name"]},"placeholder":{"template":"Select {} ...","variables":["name"]},"order":"","andSearch":false,"rangeSearch":false,"values":{"Yes":{"display":"✅"},"No":{"displayHtml":"<span class=\"status status-no\">✖</span>"},"[3] Mid-range plan with capped pre-existing limit of AED 150,000 and moderate maternity/dental sub-limits":{},"[2] Entry-level basic plan with minimal disclosed benefits and restricted to low-income dependents.":{},"[2] Basic entry-level coverage with salary-capped eligibility and limited benefit detail disclosed in source.":{},"[2] Limited information provided with most benefit details requiring reference to table of benefits document":{},"[3] Insufficient detail provided in rate chart extract to assess coverage depth and network quality":{},"[3] Limited source data with only basic coverage parameters specified":{},"[3] Mid-range worldwide coverage with limited visible benefit details in rate chart excerpt":{},"[2] Insufficient detail in source document to assess comprehensive coverage; only basic limits and copay structure visible":{},"[2] Insufficient data to assess - source only contains basic limits without network, copay, or condition details.":{},"[2] Limited information available; source lacks critical benefit details including maternity, pre-existing conditions, and network specifications.":{},"[2] Insufficient detail for comprehensive evaluation; only aggregate limit, dental cap, and territorial scope specified.":{},"[2] Limited benefit details available with worldwide coverage but sparse information on key limits and conditions":{},"[2] Insufficient benefit details in source for proper evaluation":{},"[2] Limited information available with no network, room type, maternity or pre-existing condition details disclosed in rate chart.":{},"[3] Mid-tier plan with worldwide coverage and high annual limit but incomplete benefit details in source":{},"[2] Limited information available in source document; only basic coverage parameters and dental limit specified":{},"[2] Limited information available with only basic coverage parameters disclosed and significant details missing regarding network access, maternity benefits, and pre-existing condition coverage":{},"[2] Limited information available; premium summary lacks benefit details and sub-limits.":{},"[1] Minimal coverage plan with 12-month waiting period and no disclosed benefit limits or sub-limits":{},"[2] Basic territorial coverage with restrictive network and minimal disclosed benefit limits":{},"[3] Mid-range coverage with worldwide scope and private room standard, but restricted by Super Restricted network and moderate sub-limits for maternity (AED 10,000), dental (AED 3,500), and dialysis (AED 60,000).":{},"[3] Mid-range plan with capped pre-existing limit (AED 150,000) and moderate ancillary benefits (dental AED 1,500, optical AED 1,000).":{}}}},{"Reason":{"name":"Reason","type":"LABEL","search":true,"table":true,"detail":true,"description":{"template":"Default description for {}","variables":["name"]},"placeholder":{"template":"Select {} ...","variables":["name"]},"order":"","andSearch":false,"rangeSearch":false,"values":{"Yes":{"display":"✅"},"No":{"displayHtml":"<span class=\"status status-no\">✖</span>"},"The plan offers worldwide coverage with a respectable AED 1 million aggregate limit and comprehensive benefits including organ transplant (AED 100,000 sub-limit), but the pre-existing condition cap of AED 150,000 and mandatory medical underwriting requirement position it as a mid-tier product. Maternity and dental sub-limits are moderate (AED 10,000 and AED 3,500 respectively), while the 20% outpatient copay structure with AED 50 cap provides reasonable cost-sharing. The 0% copay on prescribed drugs is a positive feature, but overall the coverage parameters and sub-limits align with a middle-market positioning rather than premium comprehensive coverage.":{},"The source provides only premium, eligibility, network, and territorial scope information without specifying benefit limits, copays, or coverage details for key services.":{},"The source provides only high-level plan parameters (network, scope, age, eligibility) without disclosing benefit limits, copays, or pre-existing condition treatment, making it difficult to assess comprehensive value.":{},"The source document provides only basic plan parameters (coverage area, annual limit, dental) but lacks critical details on network, room type, maternity, pre-existing conditions, and most sub-limits, all requiring separate documentation":{},"The source document is a rate chart header page lacking plan-specific benefit details, copay structures, network definitions, and sub-limit information necessary for comprehensive quality assessment":{},"The source document contains minimal plan details, providing only fundamental coverage parameters without comprehensive benefit schedules or policy terms":{},"The source is a rate chart header providing basic plan parameters but lacks detailed benefit breakdowns for comprehensive quality assessment":{},"The source document is a rate chart header with minimal benefit detail; comprehensive assessment requires the referenced Table of Benefits which is not included in the extracted content":{},"The source document is a rate chart header page that provides only aggregate limit, dental benefit, and territorial scope without specifying critical plan features like network access, copayment structure, maternity coverage, or pre-existing condition handling.":{},"The source is a rate chart summary that references a separate table of benefits document, leaving most coverage details unspecified.":{},"The source is a rate chart header that lacks critical benefit details such as copays, network specifications, maternity coverage, pre-existing condition terms, and room types needed for a complete plan assessment.":{},"The source document provides minimal plan details beyond territorial scope, annual limit, and basic cost-sharing, lacking comprehensive benefit specifications needed for thorough plan comparison":{},"The rate chart provides only basic plan parameters (territorial scope, annual limit, dental cap) without network details, copays, sub-limits, or pre-existing condition terms required for comprehensive comparison.":{},"The source is a rate chart that provides only high-level coverage details without comprehensive benefit specifications necessary for full plan evaluation.":{},"The source document provides only basic plan parameters (coverage area, annual limit, dental benefit, and copay structure) but lacks detailed information on networks, room types, maternity benefits, pre-existing condition treatment, and other critical coverage specifics needed for comprehensive comparison":{},"Source provides minimal plan details with most benefit limits, network information, and coverage conditions requiring reference to a separate table of benefits not included in this extract":{},"The source document provides minimal plan details beyond aggregate limit, dental cap, and copay structure, lacking critical information about network providers, room types, maternity coverage, pre-existing conditions, and waiting periods that would be necessary for a comprehensive evaluation":{},"The source is a premium summary table that provides minimal coverage details, lacking essential information about benefit limits, copays, and terms that would allow full plan evaluation.":{},"The plan provides only basic coverage details with a restrictive 12-month waiting period and lacks transparency on key benefit limits and copay structures":{},"Geographically restricted plan excluding major emirates with limited benefit transparency and basic network tier":{},"The plan offers a high annual aggregate limit (AED 1,000,000) and worldwide coverage, which are strong features. However, the Super Restricted network significantly limits provider choice, and key benefits have relatively low sub-limits: maternity is capped at AED 10,000 per event, dental at AED 3,500 annually, and dialysis at AED 60,000. Pre-existing conditions are covered but only up to AED 150,000 and require declaration and underwriting. The 20% outpatient co-pay (max AED 50) and 10% maternity co-pay add member cost-sharing. Overall, this is a mid-tier plan suitable for families seeking basic comprehensive coverage but willing to accept network restrictions and moderate sub-limits.":{},"The plan offers worldwide coverage and reasonable aggregate limit but applies 20% coinsurance broadly, caps pre-existing conditions at AED 150,000 (below aggregate limit), and provides moderate dental/optical/alternative medicine sub-limits typical of mid-tier plans. Maternity coverage requires declaration and medical underwriting with potential premium adjustment for undeclared pregnancies.":{}}}}]}